OL,5, Peter Brook, one of the most creative  
OL,6, and controversial stage directors of   
OL,7, post-war Britain, has died aged 97.    
OL,9,FBorn in London, his stage productions, 
OL,10,Fstarring some of theatre's most        
OL,11,Fdistinguished thespians, both          
OL,12,Fenthralled and shocked audiences.      
OL,14,FHis career took in Shakespeare plays,  
OL,15,FBroadway musicals and cinema, including
OL,16,Fan adaptation of Lord of the Flies.    
OL,18,FBrook, who had lived in France since   
OL,19,F1974, died in Paris on Saturday,       
OL,20,Faccording to reports.                  
